post_text:
Parents - if you receive a letter/card in the mail that is a P-EBT card. It is from the State Department of Education & DHS. The Families First Coronavirus Response Act was established to provide meals for students during the shutdown last spring. I was told that students that are not on SNAP will receive the card with approx $250 loaded on it.
We have had inquiries and wanted to spread the word that the cards are legit and can be used to purchase food only. The school is not aware of who has or has not received the cards. Everything was done at the State Department level.

From the Graduation Committee-
Thank you to all the Senior parents, Junior class, Diania Kendall, businesses, community members, Church of God, Ministerial Alliance, and everyone along the parade route for making the Class of 2020 Celebration a success. post_text:
Senior parents, Alumni, Community members- (Please do not comment - please contact me with your input/suggestions)

As you are probably aware our Auditorium has limited seating for Graduation. I am currently working on implementing one of the following resolutions-
*Reserved seating for each students' family (4-6 seats) then open seating first come first serve
*Reserving the entire auditorium and giving each student 12-15 tickets each (depending on class size)
*Somewhere in between with a combination of both
*Leave as it has been- completely open, first come first serve

We will also have open seating in the cafeteria with live stream in there as well as on Facebook. I am asking for input from parents, alumni, community members. Please DO NOT comment on this post. Please contact me personally by stopping at the high school, calling 580-782-3343, or emailing me at treese@mangum.k12.ok.us

Please also feel free to share this post.

Mangum High School Counselor
February 12 at 11:36 AM ·

Mangum has had a long tradition of providing local scholarships, however, many of
them no longer exist. At this time, we have eight scholarships generously given by local businesses and
community organizations. As the need for higher education and career training grows, so does the need for

successful future.

We have to shut the water off again, this time were giving 48 hour notice to the public so that they can be prepared. The scheduled outage will be from 10pm Thursday night to 5am Friday morning. I am posting it on Facebook now and will send out additional posts over the next 48 hours to get the word out.

Football Fundraiser

Mangum Tiger Football
July 8, 2019 at 10:51 AM ·

Mangum Tiger Football is doing a T-Shirt Fundraiser for the 2019 Season! The fundraiser will run from July 8th - July 19th. This way we can have you your shirts by first game of the season! Junior High and High School kids will have a sheet with 3 options:
A: T-Shirt. $16
B: Long Sleeve Tee $20
C: Hoodie $28

Each can be personalized with your players last name or your name (GMA, Aunt, Mom) and number on the back! We would really appreciate your support! If you can’t find an athlete to buy a shirt I am at the Old Gym Monday-Thursday 6:30 AM - 7:00 PM!

#OWYO

shared_text:
Mangum High School Counselor
June 12, 2019 at 3:21 PM ·

This year at the high school we want to encourage and celebrate post-graduate plans and achievements. We’re planning to create a bulletin board with the graduation announcements of former students with a little information about what they’re doing now in order to encourage our current students about planning for life after high school. If you’ve given me a graduate announcement in the past, I’d love to include it on the bulletin board so we can celebrate where you are now. For those I have, I’ll private message you to get your info. If anyone would like to have their picture/story to be included, please send me a picture of you from high school (doesn’t have to be a graduation announcement) and a little information about what you did/are doing after graduation. We want to know if you’re in or have graduated from college or vocational training program, and/or what your current career is!

For anyone sending a picture with your information, please send to:

Kylie Peeler
301 N Oklahoma
Mangum, OK 73554

Or drop your picture off at the high school.

post_text:
Monday’s storm resulted in significant damage to our school farm and the softball hitting facility and field, but thankfully, there were no injuries. While we appreciate the public’s interest in donating money to Mangum Schools, please know that there will be no solicitation on the school’s part. We’ve made this decision because there is the risk that some may try to fraudulently collect money on behalf of the school over which we would have no control. If you would like to make monetary contributions, those donations are tax deductible and may be made in our business office at 400 North Pennsylvania. We are grateful for all the calls, prayers and offers of help to our district.
Again, thank you for your continued support of our school system and community.
Barbara Gahagan, Assistant Superintendent
Mangum Public Schools

post_text:
Reminder: Attention 2019 Seniors and Parents:
We will be taking 2019 senior, administrator, and senior sponsor panel pictures on August 21 in the high school cafeteria from 10:15-1:00. Please come prepared for your photo in a white t-shirt(boys) and spaghetti strap shirt(girls). Boys will be provided with tuxes and girls with photo drapes. You may have received an email from Lifetouch with incorrect date. Please disregard that date and be aware of the August 21st date. There is a $20.00 fee for this photo. We will not be taking cap and gown or casual photos on that date. If you have questions, email bstover@mangum.k12.ok.us, call Barbie Stover @ 782-3343, or private message brstover on Facebook. Please share this post with all seniors.
